phaseWiseAnalysis.description: Initial state before arc contact occurs

characteristics: Low current consistent with open circuit
details.resistance: High resistance (~849 µΩ) - contacts are open
details.travel: Gradual increase from 200 to 574 - contact approaching

phaseWiseAnalysis.diagnosticVerdict: The phase is healthy because the resistance is high and stable, averaging 849.05 μΩ with a low standard deviation of 9.34 μΩ, indicating an open circuit. The current is also low, averaging 230.53 A with a standard deviation of 5.18 A, which is consistent with the expected baseline. The travel is increasing from 200.00 mm to 574.00 mm, and the close coil is active with an average current of 4.50 A, all aligning with the 'Healthy' criteria for the Pre-Contact Travel phase.
phaseWiseAnalysis.eventSynopsis: During the pre-contact travel phase, the contacts are moving towards each other with the close coil energized, but there is no electrical conduction yet, indicated by the high resistance and low current.
phaseWiseAnalysis.name: Pre-Contact Travel

waveformAnalysis.current: Current remains stable around its open circuit baseline of 230.0 A (Avg: 230.5), reinforcing no premature electrical connection.
waveformAnalysis.resistance: Resistance is high and stable (Avg: 849.1 μΩ ≥ 750 μΩ) with flat straight-line pattern (StdDev: 9.3 μΩ ≤ ±30 μΩ), indicating proper open circuit with clean separation and no premature contact.
waveformAnalysis.travel: Travel shows a smooth, continuous increase from 200.0 mm to 574.0 mm, representing unimpeded mechanical movement.

phaseWiseAnalysis.description: Arcing contact engagement and arc initiation

characteristics: Resistance decreasing from high to low
Current increasing from low to high
details.current: Sharp rise to ~723 - current flow begins
details.travel: Continues to increase to ~709 - contacts closing

phaseWiseAnalysis.diagnosticVerdict: The 'Healthy' status is supported by the data showing a resistance range of 331.00 μΩ to 650.00 μΩ, indicating a rapid drop from a higher value (implied from the previous phase). The current also rises significantly from a lower value to a range of 402.00 A to 723.00 A. These rapid changes align with the expected behavior during arcing contact engagement as per the DCRM Phase-Wise Diagnostic Criteria Reference.
phaseWiseAnalysis.eventSynopsis: The arcing contacts engage, causing a rapid decrease in resistance and a corresponding increase in current as the closing operation progresses.
phaseWiseAnalysis.name: Arcing Contact Engagement & Arc Initiation
phaseWiseAnalysis.phaseTitle: Closing Operation — Arcing Contact Engagement & Arc Initiation

waveformAnalysis.current: Current rises sharply from 402.0 A to 723.0 A (Rise: 321.0 A), establishing conduction path.
waveformAnalysis.resistance: Resistance exhibits healthy arcing behavior: sharp drop from 650.0 μΩ to 331.0 μΩ (Range: 319.0 μΩ) with prominent high-frequency arcing spikes (StdDev: 99.7 μΩ > 80), indicating proper arc initiation as arcing contacts engage.
waveformAnalysis.travel: Travel increases smoothly from 582.0 mm to 709.0 mm.

details.current: Gradual decline from 723 to 624 - stable flow
details.resistance: Stable low resistance (~300 µΩ) - good contact

phaseWiseAnalysis.diagnosticVerdict: The 'Healthy' status is justified by the very low and stable resistance (Avg=299.99 μΩ, StdDev=4.95 μΩ) and high, constant current (Avg=692.71 A, StdDev=17.36 A). The travel is also stable at maximum (Avg=749.07 mm, StdDev=4.51 mm), confirming the breaker is fully closed. These values align with the 'Healthy' criteria, where resistance should be around the closed circuit baseline with low standard deviation, and current should be high and constant.
phaseWiseAnalysis.eventSynopsis: During the main contact conduction phase, the circuit breaker exhibits stable and low resistance with high current flow, indicating good contact integrity while Trip Coil 1 is active.
phaseWiseAnalysis.name: Main Contact Conduction
phaseWiseAnalysis.phaseTitle: Fully Closed State — Main Contact Conduction

waveformAnalysis.current: Current remains high and stable, around 715.0 A (Avg: 692.7).
waveformAnalysis.resistance: Resistance maintains a healthy flat plateau at low values (Avg: 300.0 μΩ) with minimal deviation.
waveformAnalysis.travel: Travel remains perfectly stable at its maximum stroke of approximately 750.0 mm.

phaseWiseAnalysis.description: Main contact parting and arc elongation

details.current: Sharp drop from 515 to 230 - current flow stops
details.resistance: Rising from 330 to 850 µΩ - contacts separating
details.travel: Sharp drop from 723 to 200 - contacts opening

phaseWiseAnalysis.diagnosticVerdict: The phase is healthy because the resistance increases from a minimum of 330.00 μΩ to a maximum of 850.00 μΩ, indicating a smooth, near-linear rise as expected. The current decreases steadily from a maximum of 515.00 A to a minimum of 230.00 A. Travel also decreases smoothly from 200.00 mm to 723.00 mm. Trip coil 1 is active with an average current of 5.50 A, confirming proper trip initiation, all aligning with healthy criteria.
phaseWiseAnalysis.eventSynopsis: The main contacts separate, initiating arc elongation while the current decreases and the breaker begins to open, indicated by decreasing travel and trip coil activation.
phaseWiseAnalysis.name: Main Contact Parting & Arc Elongation
phaseWiseAnalysis.phaseTitle: Opening Operation — Main Contact Parting & Arc Elongation

waveformAnalysis.current: Current drops steadily from 515.0 A to 230.0 A.
waveformAnalysis.resistance: Resistance rises smoothly and progressively from 330.0 μΩ to 850.0 μΩ.
waveformAnalysis.travel: Travel decreases smoothly from 723.0 mm to 200.0 mm.

details.resistance: High resistance (~850 µΩ) - contacts fully open

phaseWiseAnalysis.diagnosticVerdict: Analysis based on programmatic data: Healthy. (LLM enhancement failed)
phaseWiseAnalysis.name: Final Open State

waveformAnalysis.current: Current remains stable around its open circuit baseline.
waveformAnalysis.resistance: Resistance remains high and stable (Avg: 850.0 μΩ).
waveformAnalysis.travel: Travel remains stable at the fully open position.

Check damping system for hydraulic oil degradation, leaks, seal failure, or piston wear.

actions.justification: The opening time is at the upper limit (40ms), suggesting potential early-stage mechanism sluggishness or increased friction that could worsen.
actions.title: Comprehensive Mechanism Lubrication & Adjustment
whatToLookFor: Inspect all moving parts, pivots, and sliding surfaces for signs of wear, corrosion, or inadequate lubrication.
Clean and re-lubricate all critical components of the operating mechanism with appropriate grease.
Adjust linkages and contact pressure to optimize mechanical advantage and ensure smooth, consistent operation.
Verify opening time and speed consistency across all poles after lubrication and adjustments.

actions.justification: The extreme contact travel (550mm) and overspeed (6.92 m/s) indicate a severe operating mechanism or damping system malfunction, risking catastrophic mechanical damage.
actions.title: Investigate and Rectify Operating Mechanism Overtravel/Overspeed
whatToLookFor: Inspect damping system for hydraulic oil leaks, piston wear, or gas spring degradation.
Verify operating spring adjustments and linkage integrity for proper stroke and timing.
Measure contact gap, overtravel, and contact pressure to ensure mechanical limits are respected.
Trigger corrective action if overtravel exceeds 200mm or speed exceeds 6.0 m/s.

actions.justification: Trip Coil 2 is completely non-functional (0.0A), eliminating redundancy and creating a single point of failure for critical fault interruption, posing a severe protection risk.
actions.title: Repair or Replace Trip Coil 2
whatToLookFor: Check the control circuit wiring and auxiliary contacts for Trip Coil 2 for continuity and proper function.
Measure the resistance of Trip Coil 2 to identify open or short circuits within the coil winding.
Verify the trip coil plunger movement and ensure no mechanical binding or obstruction.
Replace the trip coil if internal damage or electrical fault is confirmed, then retest operation.

actions.justification: DLRO of 300 µΩ, high mean resistance (299.71 µΩ), severe surface roughness, and noise spikes confirm critical main contact wear, leading to overheating and potential welding.
actions.title: Overhaul Main Contacts and Interrupter Assembly
whatToLookFor: Perform a visual inspection of the main contacts for severe erosion, pitting, and material loss.
Measure contact pressure and alignment to ensure even current distribution and proper engagement.
Clean contact surfaces thoroughly and apply appropriate contact grease to reduce friction and resistance.
Replace severely worn or damaged main contacts and associated components within the interrupter.
